  <summary>5/27/1999--Introduced.
Two Strikes and You're Out Child Protection Act of 1999 - Amends the Federal criminal code to provide for mandatory life imprisonment (unless a death sentence is imposed) of a person convicted of a Federal sex offense in which a minor is the victim if the person has a prior sex conviction in which a minor was the victim.</summary>
